A driver  was on Tuesday charged with causing deaths of two pedestrians, among other counts, along Waiyaki Way by careless driving. Clintone Odanga denied all the charges before Kibera senior resident magistrate Renee Kitagwa. Odanga is accused of driving carelessly on October 9 around Mountain View, where he veered  off the road and hit a woman identified as Sharon Nasenya who died while undergoing treatment at Eagle Nursing Home. He was also charged with causing the death of Peninah Kakayi by knocking her down with the same vehicle and causing her death on the spot. On the third count, Odanga was charged with careless driving and causing serious injuries to Veronicah Kemunto. The magistrate released him on Sh100,000 cash bail with the surety. The case will be mentioned on November 4.